<br>
Not sure why you insist on this line, but here.  Just so it's clear:<br>
<br>
Nature earring thing: 1 FT<br>
Ornate boots: 3 FT (bazaar purchasable)<br>
Mental Clarity: 2 FT (6 measily AA's)<br>
Standing: 3 FT<br>
LDoN Augs: 1 FT<br>
<br>
Total: 10 mana regen = 9 mins<br>
<br>
Just doesn't seem that tough to achieve.  I didn't even focus on it until recently.  Besides, there's another 2 still from AA's, plus 2+ from LDoN if I'm ambitious.  And, there's the FT1 range item from owlbear war in Luclin (soloable about level 60).  <br>
<br>
Total: 15 regen = 6 mins<br>
<br>
Plus, you can always add 5 from tribute (5 is max, right?):<br>
<br>
Total: 21 regen =  4.3 mins<br>
<br>
Fade well. <br>
Wyndaria. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=metranon>Metranon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(6/8/04 2:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=111>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letter from SoE from Summit</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>At lv 66 fade will work. But by lv 70 everywhere you will XP all the mobs will be immune to FM.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
