<br>
I won't get into details, but for pulling a named out of a pack of mobs regardless of numbers, nothing is nearly as good as a bard.<br>
<br>
The mana cost of fade makes sure though that even for ubergeared bards, it cannot be used unless you feel like pulling a mob every 4 minutes ;p<br>
<br>
For me - at least using the Fennin script as an example, I'd single pull all the red imps first, then let monks split off a few of the trash and pull them to camp while mezzing them on the way.<br>
<br>
Bards are by far the best pullers unless you constantly need to pull from a big group of mobs in which case you will have mana issues. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=metranon>Metranon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(6/8/04 6:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=116>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: few things</span><hr size=1> also note that bards are in many ways better pullers than monks not because they have the ability to fade and clear agro, but because they have other abilities which work in tandem with clearing agro as well<br>
<br>
For instance when pulling trash to clear in Qvic, i use mezz and snare as  often as fade when splitting, if you have 3 mobs, just mez one, 2 will run toward you, snare one, the other one will outrun the snared one, so pull that one mob into camp and mez the snared one, pull the first mob you mezzed into camp...can chain pull 1 mob at a time in this way without ever resorting to fade<br>
<br>
and until you hit the level cap on lull for mobs, thats a better option for splitting them than fade by far...<br>
